---
import LearnLayout from '../../../components/LearnLayout.astro';
---
<LearnLayout
  title="5 Tips for Safely Using AI Assistants"
  description="AI is useful. These five habits keep it honest. Practical advice for anyone who uses ChatGPT, Copilot, Gemini, or other AI assistants."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="learn-hero-img" style="background-image: url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1516321318423-f06f85e504b3?w=1920&q=80')">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <h1>5 Things to Know Before Trusting AI Advice</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">AI is useful. These habits keep it honest.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Tips -->
  <div class="tips-stack">
    <section class="tip-section learn-band">
      <div class="learn-contain">
        <div class="tip-card">
          <span class="tip-number">1</span>
          <div class="tip-content">
            <h2 class="tip-title">Ask the same question in a new conversation</h2>
            <p>If an AI finally gives you the answer you wanted after a long back-and-forth, open a fresh chat and ask the same question cold.</p>
            <p>If the fresh AI refuses or gives a very different answer, the original answer was probably drift — the AI telling you what you wanted to hear. This takes 30 seconds. It works like a lie detector for AI.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="tip-section learn-band learn-band-gray">
      <div class="learn-contain">
        <div class="tip-card">
          <span class="tip-number">2</span>
          <div class="tip-content">
            <h2 class="tip-title">Be suspicious when AI stops giving warnings</h2>
            <p>Early in a conversation, AI models include caveats: "consult a professional," "this is general information," "individual situations vary." If those warnings disappear as the conversation continues, that's a red flag.</p>
            <p>The AI's limitations haven't changed. It's just stopped reminding you about them. That's when mistakes happen.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="tip-section learn-band">
      <div class="learn-contain">
        <div class="tip-card">
          <span class="tip-number">3</span>
          <div class="tip-content">
            <h2 class="tip-title">Don't use AI as your only source for high-stakes decisions</h2>
            <p>Medical dosing, legal strategy, financial planning — these are areas where being wrong has real consequences. AI can help you prepare questions for a professional. It shouldn't be the professional.</p>
            <p>Think of AI like a smart friend who reads a lot. You wouldn't let them set your medication dose or write your will. The same standard applies here.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="tip-section learn-band learn-band-gray">
      <div class="learn-contain">
        <div class="tip-card">
          <span class="tip-number">4</span>
          <div class="tip-content">
            <h2 class="tip-title">Your credentials don't make AI safer</h2>
            <p>Telling an AI you're a doctor doesn't make its medical advice better — it makes the AI less cautious with you. It can't verify your credentials. It just skips the safety rails because you sound authoritative.</p>
            <p>An AI that thinks it's talking to a nurse will share medication details it would withhold from a general user. The guardrails are gone.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="tip-section learn-band">
      <div class="learn-contain">
        <div class="tip-card">
          <span class="tip-number">5</span>
          <div class="tip-content">
            <h2 class="tip-title">Long conversations are riskier than short ones</h2>
            <p>The longer you talk to an AI, the more it adapts to you. Fresh conversations start with full safety guardrails. Long conversations erode them.</p>
            <p>For creative brainstorming, long sessions are fine. But when the stakes are high — health, money, law, safety — keep it short and direct.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="learn-band learn-band-dark">
    <div class="learn-contain-narrow" style="text-align: center">
      <h2 class="learn-h2">Want to test your AI?</h2>
      <p class="cta-desc">SAPIEN is an open standard for measuring AI behavioral safety. Test how any model handles sustained conversational pressure.</p>
      <a href="/getting-started/" class="cta-btn">Get started with SAPIEN &rarr;</a>
      <div style="margin-top: 2.5rem">
        <div class="learn-card-grid">
          <a href="/learn/" class="learn-card-link">
            <h3>Why AI safety matters &rarr;</h3>
            <p>The big picture on AI behavioral risks.</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/learn/what-is-drift/" class="learn-card-link">
            <h3>See real examples &rarr;</h3>
            <p>Watch AI go from cautious to compliant.</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/learn/what-is-memory-exploitation/" class="learn-card-link">
            <h3>How memory makes it worse &rarr;</h3>
            <p>AI personalization has a dark side.</p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</LearnLayout>

<style>
  .tips-stack {
    /* Tip sections alternate white/gray via learn-band classes */
  }
  .tip-section.learn-band {
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }
  .tip-card {
    display: flex;
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    max-width: 48rem;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .tip-number {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 3.5rem;
    height: 3.5rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-gold);
    background: #FFFBEB;
    border: 2px solid var(--color-gold);
    border-radius: 50%;
  }
  .tip-title {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    color: var(--color-slate);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }
  .tip-content p {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-text);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .tip-content p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .cta-desc {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: #94A3B8;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 32rem;
    margin-left: auto;
    margin-right: auto;
  }
  .cta-btn {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.85rem 2.5rem;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-slate);
    background: var(--color-gold);
    border-radius: 6px;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.2s, transform 0.2s;
  }
  .cta-btn:hover {
    background: #D4B275;
    transform: translateY(-1px);
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .tip-card {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 1rem;
    }
    .tip-title {
      font-size: 1.2rem;
    }
    .tip-content p {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
    }
  }
</style>
